toes.com/m/1004047_children_of_the_corn? |website=Rotten Tomatoes |publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Firestarter (film)|Firestarter]]''\n| [[Mark L. Lester]]\n| [[Firestarter (novel)|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n| [[Universal Studios]]\n| 35%<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/firestarter/ |title=Firestarter (1984) |work=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1985\n| ''[[Cat's Eye (1985 film)|Cat's Eye]]''\n| Lewis Teague\n| Based on the short stories \"[[Quitters, Inc.]]\" and \"[[The Ledge (short story)|The Ledge]]\", the rest is original work for the film. \n| [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n| 67%<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/cats_eye |title=Cat's Eye (1985) |work=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=December 9, 2017}}</ref>\n|- \n| ''[[Silver Bullet (film)|Silver Bullet]]''\n| [[Dan Attias]]\n| Based on the novel \"[[Cycle of the Werewolf]]\". \n| Paramount Pictures\n| 47%<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/stephen_kings_silver_bullet |title=Silver Bullet (1985) |work=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=December 9, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1986\n| ''[[Maximum Overdrive]]''\n| [[Stephen King]]\n| Based on the short story \"[[Trucks (short story)|Trucks]]\". \n| [[De Laurentiis Entertainment Group|De Laurentiis Entertainment]]\n| 17%<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/maximum_overdrive |title=Maximum Overdrive (1986) |work=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=December 9, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Stand by Me (film)|Stand by Me]]''\n| [[Rob Reiner]]\n| Based on the novella \"[[The Body (King novella)|The Body]]\". \n| Columbia Pictures\n| 91%<ref>{{cite web|title=Stand by Me (1986)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/stand_by_me_1986/|language=en|accessdate=2018-04-01}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1987\n| ''[[Creepshow 2]]''\n| [[:it:Michael Gornick|Michael Gornick]]\n| Based on the short story \"[[The Raft (short story)|The Raft]]\", the rest is original work for the film. \n| New World Pictures\n| 33%<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/creepshow_2/|title=Creepshow 2 (1987)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=September 5, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sort|Running Man|''[[The Running Man (1987 film)|The Running Man]]''}}\n| [[Paul Michael Glaser]]\n| [[The Running Man (novel)|Loosely based on the novel of the same name]].\n| [[TriStar Pictures]]\n| 65%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/running_man/|title=The Running Man (1987)|publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Pet Sematary (1989 film)|Pet Sematary]]''\n| [[Mary Lambert (director)|Mary Lambert]]\n| [[Pet Sematary|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n| Paramount Pictures\n| 50%<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/pet_sematary/ |title=Pet Sematary (1989) |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{sort|1990|1990s}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |1990\n|''[[Tales from the Darkside: The Movie]]''\n|[[John Harrison (director)|John Harrison]]\n|[[The Cat from Hell|Segment \"The Cat from Hell\" based on the short story of the same name.]]\n|Paramount Pictures\n|39%<ref>{{Citation|title=Tales from the Darkside: The Movie (1990)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/tales_from_the_darkside_the_movie|language=en|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Graveyard Shift (1990 film)|Graveyard Shift]]''\n| Ralph S. Singleton\n|[[Graveyard Shift (short story)|Based on the short story of the same name]].\n| Paramount Pictures\n| 13%<ref>{{cite web|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/stephen_kings_graveyard_shift|title=Graveyard Shift (1990)}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Misery (film)|Misery]]''\n| Rob Reiner\n| [[Misery (novel)|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n| Columbia Pictures\n| 90%<ref>{{rotten-tomatoes|misery|Misery}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1992\n| {{sort|Lawnmower Man|''[[The Lawnmower Man (film)|The Lawnmower Man]]''}}\n| [[Brett Leonard]]\n| [[The Lawnmower Man|Based on the novel of the same name]]. \n| [[New Line Cinema]]\n| 35%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/lawnmower_man|title=The Lawnmower Man (1992)|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1993\n| {{sort|Dark Half|''[[The Dark Half (film)|The Dark Half]]''}}\n| George A. Romero\n| [[The Dark Half|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n| [[Orion Pictures]]\n| 56%<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dark_half/| title=The Dark Half (1993) | publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] | accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref> \n|-\n| ''[[Needful Things (film)|Needful Things]]''\n| [[Fraser Clarke Heston]]\n| [[Needful Things|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Columbia Pictures\n| 31%<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/needful_things/ | title=Needful Things (1993) | publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] | accessdate=November 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1994\n| {{sort|Shawshank Redemption|''[[The Shawshank Redemption]]''}}\n| [[Frank Darabont]]\n| Based on the novella \"[[Rita Hayworth and Shawshank Redemption]]\". \n| 90%<ref>{{cite web |title=The Shawshank Redemption (1994) |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/shawshank_redemption/ |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=September 18, 2017 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170918210429/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/shawshank_redemption/ |archivedate=September 18, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1995\n| {{sort|Mangler|''[[The Mangler (film)|The Mangler]]''}}\n| [[Tobe Hooper]]\n| [[The Mangler|Based on the short story of the same name]]. \n| New Line Cinema\n| 27%<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/mangler/|title=The Mangler (1995)|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=20 January 2014}}</re