ker (director)|Mike Barker]]\n|[[The Talisman (King and Straub novel)|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n|[[Amblin Entertainment]]\n|-\n|{{sort|Tommyknockers|''[[The Tommyknockers#Adaptations|The Tommyknockers]]''}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/tommyknockers-movie-stephen-king-james-wan-universal-1202372930/|title=Universal Answers Call To Make A \u2018Tommyknockers\u2019 Movie, Wins Bidding For Stephen King Novel|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|last2=Hipes|first2=Patrick|date=2018-04-21|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-01-26}}</ref>\n|[[James Wan]]\n|[[The Tommyknockers|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n|[[Universal Pictures|Universal Studios]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Series\n! Notes\n! Distributor\n! Original network\n!RT\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1970s\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[Salem's Lot (1979 miniseries)|Salem's Lot]]''\n| [['Salem's Lot|Based on the novel of the same name]]. \n| [[Warner Bros. Television]]\n| [[CBS]]\n|89%<ref>{{Citation|title=Salem's Lot (1979)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/salems_lot_the_movie|language=en|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1990s\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[It (miniseries)|It]]''\n| [[It (novel)|Based on the novel of the same name]]. \n| Warner Bros. Television\n| [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n|70%<ref>{{Citation|title=Stephen King's It (1990)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/stephen_kings_it1990|language=en|access-date=2020-01-14}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''[[Sometimes They Come Back (film)|Sometimes They Come Back]]''\n| [[Sometimes They Come Back|Based on the short story of the same name]]. \n| CBS\n| CBS\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[The Tommyknockers (miniseries)|The Tommyknockers]]''\n| [[The Tommyknockers|Based on the novel of the same name]]. \n| [[Trimark Pictures]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" | ABC\n|8%<ref>{{Citation|title=The Tommyknoc