020-03-04}}</ref>\n|Based on the short story \u201c[[Jerusalem's Lot]]\u201d.\n|[[Epix]]\n|[[Epix]]\n|-\n|''[[Joyland (King novel)#Adaptation|Joyland]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/stephen-king-joyland-novel-adapted-tv-series-freeform-1202492978/|title=Stephen King\u2019s \u2018Joyland\u2019 Novel Being Adapted For TV At Freeform|last=Petski|first=Denise|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|date=2018-10-31|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref>\n|[[Joyland (King novel)|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n|Freeform\n|[[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]]\n|-\n|''[[Lisey's Story (miniseries)|Lisey's Story]]''\n|[[Lisey's Story|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n| Warner Bros. Television\n|[[Apple TV+]]\n|-\n|''[[Sleeping Beauties (novel)#Adaptations|Sleeping Beauties]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/stephen-king-owen-king-sleeping-beauties-amc-series-1202596914/|title=AMC Makes Pilot Script Deal For Owen & Stephen King Novel \u2018Sleeping Beauties;\u2019 Owen King To Write It|last=Jr|first=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|date=2019-04-16|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/amc-developing-projects-katie-couric-ilana-glazer-stephen-king-scott-z-burns-1202833185/|title=AMC Networks & Studios Developing Projects With Katie Couric, \u2018The Report\u2019s Scott Z. Burns, \u2018Broad City\u2019s Ilana Glazer & Stephen King \u2013 TCA|last=White|first=Peter|last2=White|first2=Peter|date=2020-01-16|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-01-20}}</ref>\n|[[Sleeping Beauties (novel)|Based on the novel of the same name]].\n|Sugar23\n|[[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]]\n|-\n| ''[[The Stand (upcoming miniseries)|The Stand]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/horror/2019/09/13/the-stand-adaptation-director-shares-teaser-announce-start-production|title=The Stand Adaptation Director Shares Teaser to Announce Start of Production|website=www.comicbook.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-15}}</ref>\n| [[The Stand|Based on the novel of the same name]]. \n| CBS Television Distribution\n| [[CBS]]\n|-\n|[[Overlook (TV series)|''Overlook'']]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/the-shining-tv-series-overlook-jj-abrams-hbo-max/|title='The Shining' Spinoff Series 'Overlook' in the Works at J.J. Abrams' Bad Robot, HBO Max|last=Sneider|first=Jeff|date=2020-04-16|website=Collider|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n|Spin-off series based on [[The Shining (novel)|''The Shining'']]\n|Warner Bros. Television\n|[[HBO Max]]\n|}\n\n==Derivative works==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Films\n! Director\n! Notes\n! Distributor\n! [[Rotten Tomatoes|RT]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1980s\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[A Return to Salem's Lot]]''\n| [[Larry Cohen]]\n| Sequel to the ''[[Salem's Lot (1979 miniseries)|Salem's Lot]]'' miniseries. \n| [[Warner Bros.]]\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1990s\n|- \n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1992\n| ''[[Pet Sematary Two]]''\n| [[Mary Lambert (director)|Mary Lambert]]\n| Sequel to 1989's ''[[Pet Sematary (1989 film)|Pet Semetary]]''. \n| [[Paramount Pictures]]\n| 25%<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/pet_sematary_ii/ |title=Pet Sematary Two (1992) |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango (company)|Fandango]] |accessdate=2015-02-08}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Children of the Corn II: The Final Sacrifice]]''\n| David Price\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Sequel to 1984's ''[[Children of the Corn (1984 film)|Children of the Corn]]''. \n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Dimension Films]]\n| 22%<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/children_of_the_corn_ii_the_final_sacrifice/|title=Children of the Corn II: The Final Sacrifice (1993)|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=March 30, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[Children of the Corn III: Urban Harvest]]''\n| James D. R. Hickox\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n|